%spark.pyspark
from pyspark.sql import DataFrame
from pyspark.sql import functions as F
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

%pyspark
def plot_errors(test_errors,num_points,step):
    plt.xlabel('max_depth')
    plt.plot(np.arange(1, num_points+1, step),[ t for t in test_errors])
    plt.legend(('avgMetrics'),
               loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(np.arange(1,num_points+1,step))
    plt.show()

val base_path = "s3://zillowpredict/dataset"
val model_path = "s3://zillowpredict/dataset/demotest"
val out_path = "s3://zillowpredict/dataset/demotest"
val (properties, train1, train2) = PreProcessingUtils.getrawdf(base_path, spark)
val train = PreProcessingUtils.get_XY_raw(properties, train1, train2).cache() 
val featuresCols = train.drop("logerror").columns
z.put("train",train)
